2. Definitions
Personal Use: Use by a natural person exclusively for private, non-commercial purposes and not for the benefit of any third party.
Commercial Use: Any use that intends, directly or indirectly, to obtain monetary compensation, increase profit, or is part of business operations, including use by or within businesses, institutions, or non-personal entities.
Organizational Use: Any use within companies, authorities, schools, clubs, or similar legal entities, regardless of profit intent.
Modification: Any alteration, adaptation, translation, or derivative work based on the Software.
Distribution: Making the Software (in modified or unmodified form) available to third parties by any means, including uploading to public or private servers or sharing within organizations.

3. Permissions
Use: The Software may be used, unmodified, for personal, educational, or nonprofit purposes only. Modification for personal use is permitted if not distributed or used in organizations or commercial contexts.

Extensions and Integration: Third parties may develop integrations, plugins, or add-ons via official public APIs/interfaces and connect the Software with commercial or closed-source systems, provided the core Software remains unaltered and the original author (see §6) is visibly credited.

4. Restrictions
Prohibited Commercial Use: Any commercial or organizational use of the Software, except via permitted API/plugin integration without modification of the core, is prohibited.
Core Modification: Distributing, deploying, or using a modified version of the core Software in organizational or commercial contexts is prohibited. Redistribution must keep the Software fully intact, unaltered unless explicitly permitted above.

5. Attribution Requirement
Every permitted use must visibly credit the author:
